{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3647828,"name":"Kalimul","username":"Kalimul","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/a6a055/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-06-07T04:24:19.793Z","cooked":"<p>Hi, I’m a programmer on StuyPulse 694 and was looking for advice on getting port-forwarding working on our two limelights. For reference, we have two LL4’s on our robot this year, and I’ve been unable to get port-forwarding working properly.</p>
<p>I’m able to pull up the limelight API/UI for one of our cameras, but am unable to access it for the other. However I am still able to pull up the stream for this other limelight. For reference, this is the code I have in Robot Init.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">// Allows us to see the limelight feeds even while tethered through USB-B
       for (int port = 5800; port &lt;= 5809; port++){  
           PortForwarder.add(port, "10.6.94.11", port);
           PortForwarder.add(port+10, "10.6.94.12", port);
       }
</code></pre>
<p>I’m able to access the feed with the Limelight API with the IP address ending in .11 with the port at 5801, but when going to the ports on the Limelight ending at .12, (5810, 5811, 5812) I either get no response or I’m only able see the actual camera stream (without the API). This has been inconvenient all throughout our season, and any advice would be greatly appreciated!</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":3,"updated_at":"2025-06-07T04:24:19.793Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":10,"reads":168,"readers_count":167,"score":88.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":502882,"topic_slug":"help-with-port-forwarding-ll4s","display_username":"Kalimul","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":67130,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/help-with-port-forwarding-ll4s/502882/1","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3647914,"name":"Rahul Yarlagadda","username":"Knufire","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/knufire/{size}/67820_2.png","created_at":"2025-06-07T13:55:07.817Z","cooked":"<p>We did nearly the same thing and it worked for us, the difference being that we mapped ports a bit further away from the first limelight. There might be some undocumented port usage causing a conflict?</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">for (int port = 5800; port &lt;= 5809; port++) {
    PortForwarder.add(port, "10.74.57.11", port);
    PortForwarder.add(port + 100, "10.74.57.12", port);
}
</code></pre>
<p>Now that being said, there seemed to be some hardcoded port numbers internal on the Limelight dashboard, as the dashboard on the second camera would bring up the feed for the first camera. We didn’t want to find out the hard way if this could also cause settings changed in the dashboard to be pushed to the wrong Limelight, and so we ended up doing any pipeline tuning tethered over ethernet anyway.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":3,"updated_at":"2025-06-07T13:55:07.817Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":121,"readers_count":120,"score":44.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":502882,"topic_slug":"help-with-port-forwarding-ll4s","display_username":"Rahul Yarlagadda","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":12760,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"7457 Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/help-with-port-forwarding-ll4s/502882/2","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3647949,"name":"Ryan Blue","username":"Ryan_Blue","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/ryan_blue/{size}/174016_2.png","created_at":"2025-06-07T15:29:18.149Z","cooked":"<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="Kalimul" data-post="1" data-topic="502882">
